// using ~ on a non-distribution value is an error
Real x = 5.0
Real y ~ x
Real z ~ 5.0

// EXPECT AST
// (AS Real x 5.0)
// (DR Real y x)
// (DR Real z 5.0)
// EXPECT AST

// EXPECT TYPE_ERRORS
// Expression after `~' is not a distribution. After '~', you always need to provide a distribution. Do you want use `=` instead?
// Expression after `~' is not a distribution. After '~', you always need to provide a distribution. Do you want use `=` instead?
// EXPECT TYPE_ERRORS
